All In The Family
I was on assignment in the Maasai Mara (Kenya) when I stumbled on a family of four giraffes grazing in the field head-down. I wasn't anticipating this, but as soon as I raised the camera to my eye, they immediately sensed my presence and stared me down. Kind of like Kanye when the paparazzi are chasing him! And Wow! This iconic shot which I call "POV" and is also part of my Limited Edition fine art collection.
.
📷@treeoflightphotography 
.
his young man is finally about to get Dad’s attention!
.
📸 @treeoflightphotography
.

.
"Hey Taxi!" is from my award-winning street photography collection. The pigeon in the foreground steals the shot!
.

"When we don't do what we were created to do, we leave room for someone else to do it that should be doing something else." -Greg Pai
.
I have had three amazing careers, each more successful than the next, but photography has always been on my heart and I actually think I am pretty good at it. So, that is the WHY of why I am a photographer. I am doing what I was designed to do!
.

I just photographed two 4 year olds and I need a drink or three. The scene was Louisville versus Kentucky and they were both MAD! They were a blast and I only dropped one camera and knocked over one light stand the entire session! Lol! Nevertheless, I do a lot of work for this lcient and they are simply wonderful! I am happy to make unique memories of a lifetime for them. I did suggest the next time they call me should be for the kids' weddings... 😮
.
📸 @treeoflightphotography

Nothing beats shooting in the field. Reportage photography to the experienced photographer is what food was to Anthony Bourdain. Photography and more specifically, imagery can connect every dot on this planet. It can fit a square peg into a round anything. A single photograph can shrink the world into your peripheral vision and turn the imagination into reality. Don't underestimate the power of an image.
.
📸 @treeoflightphotography by Greg Pai
This shot taken at a school shed in a remote village in the Maasai Mara, Kenya. These children had never seen a camera before and were entertained by what I had to share.
.

"Hair's Everything"
📸 @treeoflightphotography 
.
We have 4 kids but I always say my wife is the mother of 5. I require a good deal of maintenance and when we got married, My Amazing Mother handed her the keys. Might sound cliché, but I honestly can't find anything wrong with this woman after nearly 30 years.

I don't share much personal on social media, but I can't help but honor her before my photography fans (and yes, critics too). But this shot which I call, "Hair's Everything" is just that. This is everything to me. My family and the leader of the regime, my always beautiful wife, Lynn. ❤️
.
